{"t": "2026-04-27T00:25:36.705973+00:00", "iter": 31, "type": "tool", "name": "bash", "args": {"command": "cd /workspace && git add logalyzer/filters.py && git commit -m 'Fix url_regex_filter to use re.search instead of re.match\n\nre.match only matches at the start of the string, so a pattern like\n\"admin\" would fail to match \"/api/admin/users\" because the URL starts\nwith \"/api/\". The test test_url_regex_finds_substring_match expects\nsubstring matching behavior.\n\nSwitch to re.search which matches anywhere in the URL. Users who want\nanchored matching can still use \"^\" in their pattern (e.g. \"^/admin\").'"}, "wall_s": 0.06, "result_len": 160}
