{"t": "2026-04-27T00:26:31.497392+00:00", "iter": 37, "type": "tool", "name": "bash", "args": {"command": "cd /workspace && git add logalyzer/aggregate.py && git commit -m 'Fix by_hour to use UTC hour instead of local time\n\nThe original by_hour() called time.localtime(ts) which converts the\ntimestamp to the system local timezone. This means the same log entry\nwould be bucketed differently depending on the machine running the\nanalysis. Since all timestamps are already in UTC (parse_timestamp\nconverts to UTC), we should use e.timestamp.hour directly.\n\nThis also removes the unused import of time.'"}, "wall_s": 0.06, "result_len": 152}
