{"t": "2026-04-27T00:27:24.756987+00:00", "iter": 42, "type": "tool", "name": "bash", "args": {"command": "cd /workspace && git add logalyzer/filters.py && git commit -m 'Convert ip_allowlist from list to set for O(1) membership testing\n\nThe original ip_allowlist_filter stored the allowlist as-is (typically\na list from CLI --ip flags). The `in` operator on a list is O(n),\nmeaning each log entry requires a linear scan of the allowlist.\n\nFor large logs with multiple --ip flags, this is a measurable\nperformance regression. Converting to a set at filter construction\ntime gives O(1) lookup per entry.'"}, "wall_s": 0.06, "result_len": 168}
